frameDefinitions: A Material has been processed (generally industrially) to some Degree in order to make it more useful for some (usually implicit) function.

An Initial_element is converted into a Final_element via a process of decay, fusion, or fission which changes the number or type of hadrons (protons or neutrons) in the nucleus of the atoms that make up the Element.  '5.5 percent of nucleii decay from tritium to He3 in a year .'
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
A Payer gives up (or potentially gives up) the use of an Asset (generally money) in order to achieve an Intended_event.
The Accused enters a Plea in answer to the Charges.
In this frame a Patient is in a state of having been broken into smaller pieces.  '
frameExamples: 5.5 percent of nucleii <t>decay</t> from tritium to He3 in a year .
Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
It 'll <t>cost</t> Sandra's parents fifty grand a year for her to attend that school.
He made it clear that he would <t>plead</t> guilty to indecent assault.
listRoleDefinitions: The substance which is altered in some useful way.
A substance definable in terms of the kind(s) of atoms that make it up.
The type of <fen>Element</fen> that results from the process.
The type of <fen>Element</fen> that begins the process.
The time at which the <fen>Element</fen> undergoes the transformation.
The location where the nuclear process occurs.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is the item(s) whose price is being assessed.  <fen>Goods</fen> is usually an External Argument:
The person whose <fen>Asset</fen> is given up in order to achieve an <fen>Intended_event</fen>.  This role is often expressed as INI.
The price of or payment made for the Goods.
The event that the <fen>Payer</fen> brings about by deploying the <fen>Asset</fen>.
The time when a transaction takes place.
The judge of the court in which the accused enters a plea.
The person entering the plea in court.
The crime with which the Accused is charged
The <fen>Plea</fen> that a defendant makes.
The <fen>Court</fen> is the institution before which the plea is entered.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
listRoleExamples: A holiday in Europe is very expensive <fex>for me</fex>.
No, they've got a special on; it's really cheap there <fex>on Tuesdays</fex>
<fex>Joy Peterson</fex> pleaded innocent to the murder of his son.
Simpson pleaded not guilty <fex>to the murder of his wife</fex>.
The student pleaded <fex>guilty</fex> to stealing a bike.
